vLLM 0.25.0 cannot serve Olmo-3 with transformers>=5: KeyError: 'rope_theta'.

vLLM routes Olmo3ForCausalLM -> models/olmo2.py (registry.py:173), whose Olmo2Attention expects a
FLAT `config.rope_parameters`. transformers 5.13's Olmo3Config always nests rope_parameters by layer
type ({'full_attention': {yarn...}, 'sliding_attention': {'rope_type':'default','rope_theta':...}}),
so `config.rope_parameters["rope_theta"]` KeyErrors on every sliding-attention layer. vLLM pins
transformers>=5.5.3 with no upper bound, so nothing catches it.

The fix is a 1:1 translation, not a guess: vLLM already derives its sliding/full branch from
config.layer_types[layer_idx] == "sliding_attention" -- the SAME layer-type keys transformers now
uses to nest rope_parameters. Flat (Olmo2) configs keep the original path.

Apply to: /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/vllm/model_executor/models/olmo2.py (~line 139)

--- a/vllm/model_executor/models/olmo2.py
+++ b/vllm/model_executor/models/olmo2.py
@@ -139,10 +139,16 @@
         # Rotary embeddings. Rope scaling is only applied on full attention layers.
-        if sliding_window is None:
-            rope_parameters = self.config.rope_parameters
-        else:
-            rope_theta = self.config.rope_parameters["rope_theta"]
-            rope_parameters = {"rope_type": "default", "rope_theta": rope_theta}
+        # transformers>=5 nests rope_parameters per layer type (Olmo3); older/Olmo2
+        # configs keep it flat.
+        _rp = self.config.rope_parameters
+        if "full_attention" in _rp or "sliding_attention" in _rp:
+            _key = "full_attention" if sliding_window is None else "sliding_attention"
+            rope_parameters = _rp[_key]
+        elif sliding_window is None:
+            rope_parameters = _rp
+        else:
+            rope_theta = _rp["rope_theta"]
+            rope_parameters = {"rope_type": "default", "rope_theta": rope_theta}
         self.rotary_emb = get_rope(
             self.head_dim,
             max_position=self.max_position_embeddings,
             rope_parameters=rope_parameters,
         )
